'''Juan José Cáceres''' (born 1 June 2000) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)#Full-back|right-back]] for [[Russian Premier League]] club [[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]].<ref name="SW1">{{Soccerway|juan-jose-caceres/650034}}</ref> Born in Argentina, he plays for the [[Paraguay national football team|Paraguay national team]].

==Career==
Cáceres spent eight years in the youth system of [[Boca Juniors]], prior to departing to join [[Racing Club de Avellaneda|Racing Club]]'s academy at the start of 2017.<ref name="IN1">{{cite news|title=Quién es Juan José Cáceres, la promesa de Racing que se tomó a golpes de puño con Centurión|url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/2019/04/18/quien-es-juan-jose-caceres-la-promesa-de-racing-que-tomo-a-golpes-de-puno-con-centurion/|accessdate=15 November 2020|work=Infobae|date=18 April 2019}}</ref><ref name="RDA1">{{cite news|title="Sueño con asistir a Lisandro"|url=https://www.racingdealma.com.ar/2017/05/30/quiero-asistir-a-lisandro/|accessdate=15 November 2020|work=Racing de Alma|date=30 May 2017}}</ref> In his second year, Cáceres was involved in a training ground fight with [[Ricardo Centurión]].<ref name="IN2">{{cite news|title=Otro escándalo de Ricardo Centurión: se agarró a trompadas con un juvenil en la reserva|url=https://www.infobae.com/deportes-2/2019/04/18/otro-escandalo-de-ricardo-centurion-se-agarro-a-trompadas-con-un-juvenil-en-la-reserva/|accessdate=15 November 2020|work=Infobae|date=18 April 2019}}</ref> His breakthrough into the Racing first-team occurred in 2020, with the right-back initially appearing as an unused substitute for a [[Argentine Primera División|Primera División]] draw with [[Club Atlético Colón|Colón]] on 14 February.<ref name="SW1"/> Cáceres' senior debut soon arrived in the succeeding November, as he featured for the second half of a home defeat to [[Arsenal de Sarandí]].<ref name="SW1"/>

On 19 February 2025, Cáceres signed a contract until the end of 2029 with Russian club [[FC Dynamo Moscow|Dynamo Moscow]], joining his compatriots [[Fabián Balbuena]] and [[Roberto Fernández (footballer, born 2000)|Roberto Fernández]] in Dynamo's defense.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=FC Dynamo Moscow|url=https://fcdynamo.ru/news/xuan-kaseres-stal-futbolistom-dynamo/|title=Хуан Касерес стал футболистом "Динамо"|date=19 February 2025|language=ru}}</ref>

==Personal life==
Cáceres is of Paraguayan descent.<ref name="IN1"/><ref name="IV1">{{cite news|title=De amigo a enemigo: quién es Juan José Cáceres, el chico de 18 años que se peleó con Ricardo Centurión|url=https://www.infoveloz.com/post/de-amigo-a-enemigo-quien-es-juan-jose-caceres-el-chico-de-18-anos-que-se-peleo-con-ricardo-centurion_155903|accessdate=15 November 2020|work=Info Veloz|date=18 April 2019}}</ref> In August 2020, it was revealed that he had tested positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]] amid the [[COVID-19 pandemic|pandemic]]; he was asymptomatic.<ref name="EPG1">{{cite news|title=Juan José Cáceres, el único positivo de Covid-19 del plantel|url=https://www.elprimergrande.com/noticia/juan-jose-caceres-el-unico-positivo-del-plantel-racing-club-el-primer-grande/|accessdate=15 November 2020|work=El Primer Grande|date=10 August 2020}}</ref><ref name="DEPO1">{{cite news|title=El juvenil de Racing, Juan José Cáceres, dio positivo de Covid-19|url=https://www.depo.com.ar/futbolargentino/El-juvenil-de-Racing-Juan-Jose-Caceres-dio-positivo-de-Covid-19-20200810-0017.html|accessdate=15 November 2020|work=DEPO|date=10 August 2020}}</ref><ref name="ESPN1">{{cite news|title=Juan José Cáceres: "Estuve bajoneado porque me había dado positivo"|url=https://www.espn.com.ar/futbol/argentina/nota/_/id/7316680/juan-jose-caceres-estuve-bajoneado-porque-me-habia-dado-positivo|accessdate=15 November 2020|work=ESPN|date=20 August 2020}}</ref>

